comment: If either ` A ` and ` C ` are the same or ` C ` follows ` A ` in the transitive closure of ` R ` _and_ ` B ` is the successor to ` C ` , then either ` A ` and ` B ` are the same or ` A ` follows ` B ` or ` B ` and ` A ` in the transitive closure of ` R ` . Similar to Proposition 111 of [Frege1879] p. 75. Compare with ~ frege111 . (Contributed by RP, 15-Jul-2020.)
